# Pet Care AI - Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values

# ============================================
# SUPABASE CONFIGURATION (Required for online mode)
# ============================================
# Get these from your Supabase project settings: https://supabase.com/dashboard
# Navigate to: Settings → API
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key-here

# ============================================
# GOOGLE GEMINI API KEY (Optional)
# ============================================
# The AI Assistant will use fallback responses if this is not provided
# Get your API key from: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
EXPO_PUBLIC_GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key-here

# ============================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================
# 1. Create a Supabase project at https://supabase.com
# 2. Copy your Project URL and anon/public key from Settings → API
# 3. Run the SQL schema from supabase-schema.sql in your SQL Editor
# 4. Configure Google OAuth in Authentication → Providers
# 5. (Optional) Get Gemini API key for AI features
# 6. Copy this file to .env and fill in your values
# 7. Restart your development server

# ============================================
# OFFLINE MODE
# ============================================
# If Supabase is not configured, the app will run in offline mode
# with mock data and no authentication required.

# Development Notes:
# - All variables prefixed with EXPO_PUBLIC_ are exposed to the client
# - Never commit your actual .env file with real credentials
# - Restart expo server after changing environment variables